comment: Mild front that eases into an oaky body and finishes with clean vanilla notes
Very smooth. Notes of oak and caramel. Delicious
I get the sour fruit nose that I love about Woodinville and great oakiness. unfortunately my pallet doesnt get too much difference from their regular bourbon on my first sample. I will return!
I’m not sure what the hype is all about...
Like sucking on a 2x4...in a good way. Heavy woods, sweetness and smooth
